<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODNOTE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
YOUNG FINDS RIGHT HOME RUN STROKE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Los Angeles Dodgers usually worry when leadoff
man Eric Young hits a home run. It typically throws off his swing
for a while. They don't want the little man to think too big.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday was different, especially after Young's eighth-inning
home run off Denny Neagle gave the Dodgers a 1-0 victory over the
Atlanta Braves.
</P>
<P>
   It was his second in two games and gave him 14 hits in the
Dodgers' nine-game homestand. But in between home runs, Young flied
out four times and popped out once.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every team I play for, they always get on me about that,''
said Young, who has four this year and 37 in his six-year career.
``They think about it a lot. I guess I do, too. My game usually is
keeping the ball on the ground and making things happen.''
</P>
<P>
   Although the Dodgers were 13 for 66 (.197) with runners in
scoring position during the homestand, Young was not part of the
problem, having four consecutive multihit games until going 1 for 4
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   He had a four-hit game against Florida on Tuesday, but No.2
hitter Mark Grudzielanek went 0 for 5 and the Dodgers lost.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is as good as I have felt in a long time,'' said Young,
who has missed 32 starts this year with a strained left thigh.
``This is what we need to get things going, getting me on base.''
</P>
<P>
   Dodgers manager Glenn Hoffman said he could tell Young went for
a bigger swing after homering Saturday in the fifth inning.
</P>
<P>
   ``We were saying on the bench that he was starting to pull his
front arm out after the first home run,'' Hoffman said. ``But
today, he just laid the bat on the ball. It was perfect.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Quick hits: The Dodgers failed to score in Darren Dreifort's
seven innings of work, giving him just 61 runs in 1641/3 innings
(3.34 runs per game), third lowest in the NL. Teammate Carlos Perez
has the lowest.... The victory snapped a losing streak against the
Braves at eight games. The two teams play next weekend in Atlanta
as part of a seven-game Dodgers trip that begins Tuesday night in
Pittsburgh.... When Andres Galarraga was hit by a Dreifort pitch in
the second inning, it was the 20th time that has happened this
season. That ties Jeff Blauser's single-season club record. He has
132 lifetime, most among active players.... Scott Radinsky began
the eighth inning and retired the Braves in order. Coming in,
Radinsky had allowed 17 of 34 inherited base runners to score....
Two hits by the Braves tied a season low.... They are 82-42, the
best record in the NL.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
