   CLINTON-STARR-RDP (Washington) _ The president's senior advisers
late Sunday secured his agreement to acknowledge to a federal grand
jury on Monday that he engaged in an inappropriate physical
relationship with Monica Lewinsky, but he will deny that he
counseled her or anyone else to lie about their relationship, said
an adviser familiar with the preparations for Clinton's testimony.
By John M. Broder and James Bennet. (With graphic.)
