Clinton's wife, friends and closest political allies, Kenneth
Starr's prosecutors on Monday confront Clinton himself, the
ultimate target of an inquiry that began four years ago with an
Arkansas land deal that few Americans could fathom and became a sex
scandal most Americans say they would rather forget. By Don Van
Natta and Francis X. Clines. (With graphic.)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-TOBACCO (Washington) _ Rebuffed by a federal court in
their effort to regulate tobacco products, Clinton administration
officials said they are seriously considering lawsuits against
cigarette companies to recover money spent by the government in
treating smokers under Medicare and other federal health programs.
By Robert Pear.
