</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Investors weigh the impact of the Russian
devaluation, the Clinton testimony and another decline on the Tokyo
market. At 1:50 p.m., the Dow industrial average was up 91 points.
In Asia, Tokyo shares fell 2.2 percent. Prices were down 0.8
percent in Frankfurt and up 0.3 percent in London. On the American
debt market, the long bond was up 2/32 point at midday, with the
yield at 5.54 percent. By Sharon R. King.
</P>
