<P>
   INITIATIVE-AFFIRMATIVE-ACTION (Undated) Two years ago, in the
aftermath of California's passage of Proposition 209, it seemed
much of the nation was on the verge of following the Golden State's
lead and repealing affirmative action. Legislatures in 16 states
considered eliminating programs that take race and gender into
account in government hiring, contracting or school admissions.
Citizens in at least six states mounted signature-gathering drives
seeking to end affirmative action programs. But all those statewide
efforts have faltered, with one exception: Washington state. Voters
in Washington state will be asked to decide Nov. 3 whether to
abolish preferences for women and minorities designed to overcome
historic racial and sexual discrimination.
