<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Some famous May-December romances
 &HT;    By Alma E. Hill
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Among celebrities, older men and younger women are the norm. But
some well-known women have bucked the trend:
</P>
<P>
   -- Susan Sarandon, 51, whose common-law husband, Tim Robbins, is
39.
</P>
<P>
   -- Pam Grier, 49, whose fiance, Kevin Evans, is 36.c
</P>
<P>
   -- Barbra Streisand, 56, who had a fling with Andre Agassi, 28.
</P>
<P>
   -- Ursula Andress, 62, who was romantically involved with Harry
Hamlin, 46.
</P>
<P>
   -- Francesca Annis, 54, whose companion is Ralph Fiennes, 35.
</P>
<P>
   -- Elizabeth Taylor, 66, whose latest ex-husband is Larry
Fortensky, 46.
</P>
<P>
   -- Glenn Close, 51, who once dated Woody Harrelson, 37.
</P>
<P>
   -- Cher, 52, who had a string of younger guys, including Richie
Sambora, 39; Tom Cruise, 36; and Val Kilmer, 38.
</P>
<P>
   -- Fashion designer Mary McFadden, who was 58 when she married
for the seventh time to Vasilis Calitsis, then 31.
</P>
<P>
   -- Mary Tyler Moore, who wed heart surgeon Robert Levine, 16
years her junior, in 1983.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
