<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Crowes compilation isn't in demand
 &HT;    By Russ DeVault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Black Crowes, Atlanta-born rockers looking to jump-start
their careers, are hoping the release of the five-disc box set
``Sho' Nuff'' will trigger interest in ``By Your Side,'' the
group's fifth album and first for Columbia that's due Nov. 17.
</P>
<P>
   Neither HMV Music, asking $47.99 for the set, nor Best Buy,
where the price is $35.99, reports much demand for the set in the
Atlanta area. It contains remastered versions of the Crowes' four
albums with a couple of bonus tracks on each, some videos and an EP
with five unreleased tunes recorded during a 1995 show at the
Beacon Theatre in New York City.
</P>
<P>
   -- Cam'ron, ``Confessions of Fire'' (Untertainment Records).
Grade: C+
</P>
<P>
   -- Hootie &AMP; the Blowfish, ``Musical Chairs'' (Atlantic). Due
Sept. 15.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``How Stella Got Her Groove Back'' soundtrack (Flyte Tyme).
Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   -- Korn, ``Follow the Leader'' (Immortal/Epic). Grade: C+
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Notwist,'' Shrink'' (Zero Hour). German quartet with
Sonic Youth-meets-Metallica sound looks for trend-setting North
American breakthrough.
</P>
<P>
   -- Dolly Parton, ``Hungry Again'' (Decca). Grade: B+
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
