<SLUG> BC-EDITOR-APPOINT-1STLD-WRITETHRU </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EDITOR-HNS  
 &HT;    OF THE BEAUMONT ENTERPRISE 
</HEADLINE>
 FUENTES APPOINTED MANAGING CORRECTS 4th graf to make Corpus Christi city of birth  
 For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1998 Beaumont Enterprise  
<TEXT>
<P>
   BEAUMONT, Texas _ Diana Fuentes, regional and political editor
at the San Antonio Express-News, has been named managing editor of
The Beaumont Enterprise.
</P>
<P>
   Timothy M. Kelly, the editor of the Enterprise, announced the
appointment Monday and said she will join the newspaper August 31.
</P>
<P>
   Kelly said her professional experience, community-mindedness and
high professional standards ``make her ideally suited for leading
The Enterprise's newsroom. We were fortunate to attract a
journalist and person of Diana's caliber.''
</P>
<P>
   Fuentes, 39, a native of Corpus Christi, Texas, has worked at
the Express-News since 1989. She was the chief of the newspaper's
capital bureau in Austin for four years and has been regional
editor since 1996. She assumed the additional duties of political
editor in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Fuentes previously worked at two other Hearst newspapers in
Texas _ at the San Antonio Light as a reporter and at the Laredo
Morning Times for seven years as a reporter, magazine editor,
Sunday editor, capital correspondent and city editor.
</P>
<P>
   Fuentes is financial officer and a member of the board of
directors of the 1,500-member National Association of Hispanic
Journalists. She is a 1985 graduate of the University of Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Rivard, editor of The Express-News, said: ``Diana's
arrival in Beaumont comes at a time when Hearst newspapers in Texas
are working more closely together, sharing our news products and
our growing talent pool. Readers are the real beneficiaries because
they are getting more relevant and in-depth Texas news not
otherwise available. Diana will bring energy and experience to her
new post in Beaumont.''
</P>
<P>
   The Enterprise is the sixth-largest newspaper in the Hearst
group, serving Beaumont, 10 counties in Southeast Texas and two
parishes in Louisiana. It has a daily circulation of 60,000 and a
Sunday circulation of 72,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
