Cardinals arrived in Arizona, owner Bill Bidwell did everything
wrong. The team often was mentioned in the same breath as the
Falcons, Saints and other dregs of the NFL. Bidwell stepped back in
recent years, and Arizona has flourished. Something big is
happening in the desert. (Pasquarelli, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATORS _ The Road to College Football previews Florida. The
offseason talk at Florida has focused on the uncertainty at
quarterback with Doug Johnson and Jesse Palmer fighting for the
starting job. Johnson has admitted that he has matured over the
past year, admitting that the incident that led to the suspension
against Auburn was a mistake, and plans to devote his attention to
regaining the job full time. Palmer hasn't conceded the job to
Johnson and plans to battle for the position. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   GEORGE-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ If Mike Tyson studied
geography in addition to the teachings of ancient Chinese
philosophers during his incarceration for rape, he knows that no
matter what happens in Las Vegas, 48 states and a handful of U.S.
protectorates remain to be petitioned for a boxing license.
(George, Palm Beach Post.) MOVED.
</P>
