<P>
   MICROSOFT-RULING (Undated) Microsoft urged a federal appeals
court Monday not to allow the public to watch the government's
upcoming pre-trial interviews with Bill Gates, saying it would
create a ``carnival atmosphere.'' The company is appealing a
judge's order last week opening the depositions of Gates and other
executives in the government's antitrust case.The judge, who later
refused to reconsider his decision, cited an 85-year-old law that
requires such interviews be opened in antitrust trials.It was
unclear exactly when the U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of
Columbia might make its decision, but a ruling was expected early
this week.
</P>
<P>
   By Warren Wilson. (story will move in the ``f'' category)
