   &QL; 
GLF-ACADEMY (Los Angeles) _ Like thousands of U.S. servicemen at
the beginning of the decade, Randy Cardoza worried about his
future. After investing nine years in the Navy, budget cuts and
downsizing forced him to look for a new job. At 33, he was an
unemployed aviation electric technician with no real plan for the
rest of his life.Except that he wanted to play as much golf as
possible. Cardoza's love for golf convinced him to take a gamble
that, if it paid off, would allow him to accomplish two goals: find
a new career and satisfy his fondness for golf. Cardoza enrolled in
San Diego Golf Academy, a two-year golf management and
instructional college designed to prepare students for all facets
of the golf industry. &QL; 
By Vincent Bonsignore. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.)
