</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-BRAVES-ONDECK18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Braves on deck: San Francisco Giants
 &HT;    By I. J. Rosenberg
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ When: Tonight and Wednesday at 7:40 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   _ TV: TBS will telecast tonight's game, and Fox Sports South
will show Wednesday's game.
</P>
<P>
   _ Probable starting pitchers: Tonight, RHP Greg Maddux (15-6,
1.67, 17-10, 2.82 ERA lifetime vs. Giants) vs. LHP Kirk Rueter
(12-8, 4.44; 0-2, 5.82 lifetime vs. Braves). Wednesday, LHP Tom
Glavine (16-4, 2.35, 13-10, 3.38 ERA lifetime vs. Giants) vs. RHP
Mark Gardner (9-5, 4.89; 5-5, 4.13 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   _ Series history: The Giants lead 272-263, but the last time
they won a season series from the Braves was 1990.
</P>
<P>
   _ Past meetings: The Braves swept the Giants three games in San
Francisco a little more than a week ago and lead the season series
6-1.
</P>
<P>
   _ Giants leaders: Avg. _ Marvin Bernard (.317); HRs _ Barry
Bonds (24); RBIs _ Bonds (92); SBs - Bonds (20); Wins _ Rueter
(12); ERA - Robb Nen (1.29); Saves - Nen (31); Strikeouts - Shawn
Estes (115).
</P>
<P>
   _ Quickly: Estes, the team's top winner last season with 19
victories, remains on the disabled list with rotator-cuff problems.
. . . The Giants are seventh in the league with a 4.15 ERA. . . .
Their .270 average is fourth. . . . The Giants are on a three-game
winning streak but have won just five of their last 12 games. . . .
Second baseman Jeff Kent has reached the 20-homer mark for the
fourth time in his career. . . . The Giants have given up 140
homers, third in the NL behind the Phillies (150) and Diamondbacks
(151). . . . First baseman J.T. Snow is considering giving up
switch hitting and hitting from just the left side. As a
right-handed hitter, Snow is hitting just .169 (11-for-65) with one
homer and six RBIs. He hit .188 last year and .199 the year before.
. . . Former Brave Chris Brock is working out of the Giants bullpen
and occasionally getting a start.
</P>
<P>
   _ Who's hot: Bonds has a four-game hitting streak in which has
gone 7-for-12 with 10 RBIs. . . . Gardner is coming off a
nine-inning shutout of the Marlins.
</P>
<P>
   _ Who's not: Nen has blown two of his last five save
opportunities, and his ERA increased from 1.01 to 1.29. . . .
Rueter has lost five of his last seven decisions.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
