<HEADLINE>
LESSONS OF HAYDN FOR MADONNA
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   M &UR; adonna  &LR; and  &UR; Angela Bassett &LR;  turned 40 on Sunday, and
 &UR; Michael Jackson  &LR; will do so on August 29.
</P>
<P>
   Gerontologist  &UR; Vern Bengtson &LR;  of the University of Southern
California, commenting on this brand new phenomenon of years
passing, pointed out to Reuters that half the signers of the
Declaration of Independence were not yet 30, but wore gray wigs.
</P>
<P>
   As to the  &UR; Rolling Stones &LR; , still playing the music of their
youth, Bengtson said, ``I think it's weird, but their managers have
told them to make the Baby Boomers relive their youth instead of
building on history. It was the same in the time of Haydn. They
brought him back in an attempt to re-create the music he had done
30 years earlier, and he rebelled. So his last symphonies were
totally different.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WAVES OF THE FUTURE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ About 10 percent of McDonald's franchises are opting to sell
the fast food chain's own brand of bottled water, which means it's
a success, says Advertising Age. Promotional materials tout it as a
``natural and refreshing'' beverage to accompany fast food.
</P>
<P>
   _ A poll taken for the Visa/Plus ATM Network, reported in Jump
magazine, found that 52 percent of Americans would not want to see
a woman's face on paper currency.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Dave Caulkins &LR; , director of the Millennium Meteor Fireworks
project, told the Journal of Pyrotechnics that disarmed Russian and
American missiles, intended for nuclear bombs, could well be
renovated to produce millennium fireworks visible from almost 100
miles away, says Details magazine.
</P>
<P>
   _ The J-Allure, which costs $12,500 and is made by Jacuzzi
Whirlpool Bath, is a combination shower/hot tub/whirlpool/steam
bath, equipped with a TV, VCR, stereo and CD player, four speakers
and a remote control. ``If only it had a fridge,'' says Men's
Fitness magazine.
</P>
<P>
   _ Organizers of Burning Man festivities in Nevada are conducting
an online panty drive, the gatherings to be used as thatch-like
material for the roof of a sun-protecting hut. ``We regret,'' says
the request, ``that we will be unable to return your panties to you
as they will be burned.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; STREET SCENES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Perhaps in sympathy with downed balloonist  &UR; Steve Fossett &LR; ,
the giant advertising balloon that usually bobs over Computown at
Market and Third streets in San Francisco lay deflated on the
sidewalk Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
   _ Driving to San Francisco on 101 in Marin,  &UR; Adrienne Biggs &LR;  was
captivated by the sign on the Pacific Theatres in Corte Madera,
visible from the freeway in both directions, which had been
changed, overnight, from ``Saving Private Ryan'' to ``Pet a
Vagina.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ The Four Seasons hotel in Beverly Hills added a surcharge to
the Spice Girls' bill, reports the Chicago Sun-Times, because the
Girls were such lousy tippers. In San Francisco, on the other hand,
 &UR; David Sinclair &LR;  of Uncle Mame reports that Posh Spice,
 &UR; Victoria &LR;   &UR; Adams &LR; , cheerfully paid cash for a number of
knickknacks, including a souvenir with a picture of herself. She
said it was for her mother's collection.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Fran Capo &LR; , the world's fastest female talker, speaks at a
clip of 603.23 words a minute, reports the New York Observer.
Furthermore, Shape magazine says that the average woman eats four
pounds of lipstick in her lifetime.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I think wings are sexy. I bet if you walked outside and looked
carefully at the people around you, you could immediately tell who
has wings and who doesn't.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR; _ &LR;  Julia Roberts in InStyle magazine.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I think people may criticize horror movies as being `slasher
movies,' but there is also stuff in them that's the metaphor for
life. I think (there's) a message that I would hope is ... positive
... for anybody going through any problem.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR; _ &LR;  Jamie Lee Curtis on the importance of her oeuvre, the latest
example being ``Halloween: H20,'' quoted in Entertainment Weekly.
</P>
</TEXT>
