<HEADLINE>
ACCOUNTS AND PEOPLE IN THE ADVERTISING WORLD 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Calif., Conn., Mass., N.Y., Pa.)  (js) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Duncan Pollack, a longtime top executive at Ammirati Puris
Lintas in New York, said Sunday that he had resigned.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a great 13-year run at APL, but the time has come
for a new challenge,'' Pollack, 54, said, adding that he was
``investigating a number of opportunities'' and would announce his
plans in the near future.
</P>
<P>
   There has been speculation that Pollack would leave the agency
since he relinquished his positions as chairman and chief executive
of the New York office in January, while continuing as president
for North American operations.
</P>
<P>
   Martin Puris, chairman, chief executive and chief creative
officer at Ammirati Puris, will temporarily assume Pollack's North
American duties while a successor is sought.
</P>
<P>
   Pollack had been a top executive of Ammirati &AMP; Puris before that
agency was acquired by Interpublic Group of Cos. in 1995 and merged
with Lintas Worldwide to form Ammirati Puris Lintas.
</P>
<P>
   Two Agencies Named to a Split Fleet Account
</P>
<P>
   Fleet Financial Group said Monday that it would divide its
direct-marketing account, with billings estimated at $150 million,
between Barry Blau &AMP; Partners in Wilton, Conn., and Devon Direct in
Berwyn, Pa. The account had been handled by various agencies,
including Devon.
</P>
<P>
   Betsy Richardson, a spokeswoman for Fleet in Boston, confirmed
reports of the decision this week in Advertising Age and Adweek.
She said the decision came after a three-month review that had been
narrowed to Blau, a unit of Snyder Communications ; Devon, and two
other agencies: Bozell Direct in New York, part of True North
Communications and Cohn &AMP; Wells in New York.
</P>
<P>
   More Schwab Duties for BBDO Worldwide
</P>
<P>
   Charles Schwab &AMP; Co. in San Francisco said Monday that it had
expanded its relationship with BBDO Worldwide by naming BBDO West
in Los Angeles to handle creative duties on its Mutual One Source
mutual funds service account, with billings estimated at $30
million to $35 million. The account had been divided between Cohn
Godley Norwood in Boston, which handled the print portion, and an
in-house team, which handled the television portion.
</P>
<P>
   BBDO West, part of Omnicom Group, was awarded the assignment
without a formal review. The decision comes less than two months
after BBDO New York was awarded Schwab's consolidated brand
advertising account for financial services, with billings estimated
at $40 million to $50 million.
</P>
<P>
   Suissa Miller Advertising in Los Angeles will continue to handle
the Schwab online brokerage account, while Rubin Postaer &AMP;
Associates in Santa Monica, Calif., will continue to handle media.
</P>
<P>
   People
</P>
<P>
   Evan Sirof was named to head a new public relations division at
Marcomm Group Inc., Great Neck, N.Y., as public relations director.
He had been marketing communications manager at Scitex Digital
Video Redwood City, Calif. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
